Just thought I'd throw in about defining moments. Even as an athiest one might have one, but alas, I am not one of those. As a child, my parents were never devout in anything, my grandparents on my mothers side are devout baptists and I used to loathe going to spend the weekend with them cause they dragged me to church on sunday and frankly, it bored me to tears. I went down to the child area and got in trouble with the teachers because I coloured in a picture of jesus purple or something =) Since my grandfather passed away, my grandmother has tried converting us to religion =/ She calls us and asks us to go to church more often and such. I respect her relgion but it annoys me when she does this. She doesn't even know I'm athiest, prob give her a heart attack.<br>
<br>
I guess the defining thing that turns me off religion is I have to just believe. I just can't do it. Science, sure it can be wrong and they haven't explained everything, but there are people working on that. <br>
Then there is the fact of what some religious people do. First there is the zealots, who I just find pathetic when they suicide murder some people because 'God' said to, then there is those that push their religion on others. I <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> HATE</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that. I honestly don't care if your a satanist, just don't come trying to convert me. I don't try to convert you to athiesm, so stop trying to convert me to whatever the fuck you believe in.<br>
